    - But COMPUTING those bits takes O(x^{2/3}) TIME
    - Analogous to summing n random bits: answer is O(log n) bits, needs all n bits
    - p(n) ∈ L (logspace) → p(n) ∈ NC² (circuits depth O(log²n))
    - Circuit SIZE unknown — if polylog, polylog time follows
    - PRIMES not known to be in NC (major open problem)
    
